<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-YIOX4SFw7g2bA-L113emjA" name="organize_requirements,_d0LLYOF9Edy14KJRPqCmog" guid="-YIOX4SFw7g2bA-L113emjA" changeDate="2011-08-05T11:58:57.859-0700" version="7.2.0">
  <mainDescription>This task describes the decisions involved in organizing the project requirements. A large requirement set will quickly&#xD;
become unmanageable if it is not organized so that the analysts and other project team members can easily find them. The&#xD;
organizational&amp;nbsp;structure must be captured in the requirements management plan.</mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_vMHScHnqEd29Rtf8hOMN0w" name="Categorize requirements" guid="_vMHScHnqEd29Rtf8hOMN0w">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Assign each requirement to a requirement type from among those requirement types identified for use in the project. In&#xD;
    projects with more formality, the requirement types are specified in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.rqmts_mgmt.base-ibm/workproducts/requirements_management_process_description_AEF73456.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_D-xz4HRrEd2-O6kr4zpk8g&quot;>Requirements Management Process Description&lt;/a>. See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.rqmts_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/categorizing_requirements_8E94D048.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_Bx_TUHnpEd29Rtf8hOMN0w&quot;>Guideline: Categorizing Requirements&lt;/a> for information on how to assign requirements&#xD;
    to the proper category.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Help the stakeholders understand the requirements better by organizing them into packages or collections. Create a&#xD;
    project structure for organizing requirements and supporting artifacts. Trace requirements to the supporting artifacts.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The definition of the packages or collections is usually organization-specific, and&amp;nbsp;can sometimes be&#xD;
    project-specific. See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.rqmts_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/packaging_requirements_C30DBF2A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_jb5eoHnoEd29Rtf8hOMN0w&quot;>Guideline: Packaging Requirements&lt;/a> for more information.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_80xRUOV9Edy1IIqc4EV0PA" name="Assign attributes" guid="_80xRUOV9Edy1IIqc4EV0PA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Analyze and understand each individual requirement. As part of the initial analysis of each requirement, assign&#xD;
    requirement attribute values to each requirement. For example, assign business value (such as high, medium, or low) to&#xD;
    requirements. This improves your ability to prioritize, track and manage the requirements. Review existing attribute&#xD;
    values and update as necessary.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Attributes are defined in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.rqmts_mgmt.base-ibm/workproducts/requirements_attributes_4340F783.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_rgaGUPxiEdyNoss1L6vBPA&quot;>Artifact: Requirements Attributes&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_P_aegHntEd29Rtf8hOMN0w" name="Manage approval of requirements" guid="_P_aegHntEd29Rtf8hOMN0w">
    <sectionDescription>Work with&amp;nbsp;project manager and stakeholders to prioritize and&amp;nbsp;approve&amp;nbsp;requirements for the release, updating&#xD;
the project plan or release backlog to reflect requirements prioritization as needed. Establish traceability between items&#xD;
in the project plan or backlog&amp;nbsp;and the approved requirements for the release.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Help&amp;nbsp;monitor project progress by maintaining the status of requirements.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Package requirements so the project team&amp;nbsp;can easily&amp;nbsp;find, manage, and avoid duplication.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
